Orkjärv Nature Reserve
Location Estonia
Nearest city Tallinn
Coordinates 59°08′30″N 24°13′24″E﻿ / ﻿59.14167°N 24.22333°E﻿ / 59.14167; 24.22333Coordinates: 59°08′30″N 24°13′24″E﻿ / ﻿59.14167°N 24.22333°E﻿ / 59.14167; 24.22333
Area 748 ha (1,850 acres)
Established 2005

Orkjärv Nature Reserve is a nature reserve situated in northern Estonia, in Harju County. It was established in 2005.[1]

Nature reserve was established to protect Orkjärve Bog and Aude and Viisu mires.

  • Cygnus cygnus

  • Lake Laanemaa
